race.comment: ROYAL SILVER (3) raced back in the field on debut last start after a poor jump then quickened nicely to get up for second in soft going over 1200m at Canterbury. Only needs to tidy up her barrier manners to be going one better. LIPSTICK (8) knuckled down strongly in the closing stages to be beaten just half a length when resuming over 1200m at Warwick Farm last time out. Genuine filly who handled a heavy track when resuming last prep. Looks the obvious danger. KOKATAHI (1) is back from a six-month break. Encountered three soft tracks in the maiden prep and was in the money on each occasion. Trialling well and looks sure to make an immediate impact. PRINCE CHARGE (2) didn't stretch out on a soft track when well beaten on debut in September, his only run to date. In the market that day so has more to offer. Waller has decided to run him which is a positive sign. Market watch on FEMININO (7) on debut for Waterhouse/Bott after a good recent Randwick trial.
